.SH METHODS
.IX Header "METHODS"
.SS run
.IX Subsection "run"
.Vb 1
\&    $relay\->run(\*(Aq127.0.0.1\*(Aq, 8080);
.Ve
.PP
Starts the relay and blocks until \f(CW\*(C`stop\*(C'\fR is called. Equivalent to
calling \f(CW\*(C`start\*(C'\fR followed by a blocking event loop.
.SS start
.IX Subsection "start"
.Vb 1
\&    $relay\->start(\*(Aq127.0.0.1\*(Aq, 8080);
.Ve
.PP
Starts listening for WebSocket connections on the given host and port.
Returns immediately without blocking. Use this when you want to embed
the relay in a larger application, run a client and relay in the same
process, or compose with other AnyEvent watchers.
.PP
.Vb 3
\&    # Run a relay and client together
\&    my $relay = Net::Nostr::Relay\->new;
\&    $relay\->start(\*(Aq127.0.0.1\*(Aq, 8080);
\&
\&    my $client = Net::Nostr::Client\->new;
\&    $client\->connect(\*(Aqws://127.0.0.1:8080\*(Aq);
.Ve
.SS stop
.IX Subsection "stop"
.Vb 1
\&    $relay\->stop;
.Ve
.PP
Stops the relay, closes all connections, and clears all subscriptions.
If the relay was started with \f(CW\*(C`run\*(C'\fR, also unblocks it.
Safe to call on an unstarted relay.
.SS graceful_stop
.IX Subsection "graceful_stop"
.Vb 1
\&    $relay\->graceful_stop;
.Ve
.PP
Initiates a graceful shutdown. Stops accepting new connections immediately,
sends a \f(CW\*(C`NOTICE\*(C'\fR ("shutting down") to all connected clients, then closes
all connections after \f(CW\*(C`shutdown_timeout\*(C'\fR seconds (default: 5). This gives
clients time to reconnect to another relay.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    my $relay = Net::Nostr::Relay\->new(shutdown_timeout => 10);
\&    $relay\->start(\*(Aq0.0.0.0\*(Aq, 8080);
\&    # ... later ...
\&    $relay\->graceful_stop;  # NOTICE sent, connections close after 10s
.Ve
.SS broadcast
.IX Subsection "broadcast"
.Vb 1
\&    $relay\->broadcast($event);
.Ve
.PP
Sends the event to all connected clients whose subscriptions match.
Normally called internally when a new event is accepted. Does not store
the event \-\- use "inject_event" for storing without broadcasting, or
publish via the normal EVENT protocol flow for both.
.SS connections
.IX Subsection "connections"
.Vb 1
\&    my $conns = $relay\->connections;  # hashref (snapshot)
.Ve
.PP
Returns a shallow copy of the active connections hash. Mutating the
returned hashref does not affect the relay\*(Aqs internal state. Keys are
connection IDs, values are AnyEvent::WebSocket::Connection objects.
.SS subscriptions
.IX Subsection "subscriptions"
.Vb 1
\&    my $subs = $relay\->subscriptions;  # hashref (snapshot)
.Ve
.PP
Returns a two\-level copy of the active subscriptions hash. Mutating
the returned hashref (or its inner hashes) does not affect the relay\*(Aqs
internal state. Keys are connection IDs, inner keys are subscription
IDs, values are arrayrefs of Net::Nostr::Filter objects.
.SS store
.IX Subsection "store"
.Vb 1
\&    my $store = $relay\->store;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the storage backend object (Net::Nostr::RelayStore by default).
.SS events
.IX Subsection "events"
.Vb 1
\&    my $events = $relay\->events;  # arrayref of Net::Nostr::Event
.Ve
.PP
Returns a snapshot (array copy) of stored events, sorted by \f(CW\*(C`created_at\*(C'\fR
DESC then \f(CW\*(C`id\*(C'\fR ASC. Mutating the returned arrayref does not affect the
store. Reflects replaceable/addressable semantics (only the latest version
of each replaceable or addressable event is retained). Ephemeral events
are never stored.
.PP
Can also be used as a setter for backward compatibility. The setter clears
the store and re\-stores each event individually (duplicates are silently
skipped, and \f(CW\*(C`max_events\*(C'\fR eviction applies):
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    $relay\->events([]);                   # clear all events
\&    $relay\->events([$event1, $event2]);   # replace with given events
.Ve
.SS inject_event
.IX Subsection "inject_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $ok = $relay\->inject_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Stores an event directly into the store without validation or broadcasting.
Returns 1 on success, 0 if the event is a duplicate. Useful for tests and
programmatic seeding of relay state.
.PP
.Vb 3
\&    my $relay = Net::Nostr::Relay\->new(verify_signatures => 0);
\&    $relay\->inject_event($event);  # 1
\&    $relay\->inject_event($event);  # 0 (duplicate)
.Ve
.SS max_events
.IX Subsection "max_events"
.Vb 1
\&    my $max = $relay\->max_events;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the configured maximum event capacity, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if unlimited
(the default). This value is passed to the default store on construction.
.SS event_rate_limit
.IX Subsection "event_rate_limit"
.Vb 1
\&    my $limit = $relay\->event_rate_limit;  # e.g. \*(Aq10/60\*(Aq or undef
.Ve
.PP
Returns the per\-connection event rate limit string, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if
unlimited (the default). See "new" for token bucket semantics.
.PP
.Vb 1
\&    my $relay = Net::Nostr::Relay\->new(event_rate_limit => \*(Aq10/60\*(Aq);
.Ve
.SS verify_signatures
.IX Subsection "verify_signatures"
.Vb 1
\&    my $bool = $relay\->verify_signatures;
.Ve
.PP
Returns whether Schnorr signature verification is enabled (default: true).
.SS max_connections_per_ip
.IX Subsection "max_connections_per_ip"
.Vb 1
\&    my $limit = $relay\->max_connections_per_ip;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the maximum number of simultaneous connections allowed per IP
address, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if unlimited (the default).
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    my $relay = Net::Nostr::Relay\->new(max_connections_per_ip => 10);
\&    $relay\->start(\*(Aq0.0.0.0\*(Aq, 8080);
.Ve
.SS min_pow_difficulty
.IX Subsection "min_pow_difficulty"
.Vb 1
\&    my $min = $relay\->min_pow_difficulty;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the minimum Proof of Work difficulty required for events (NIP\-13),
or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if not set (the default).
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    my $relay = Net::Nostr::Relay\->new(min_pow_difficulty => 16);
\&    $relay\->start(\*(Aq0.0.0.0\*(Aq, 8080);
.Ve
.SS relay_url
.IX Subsection "relay_url"
.Vb 1
\&    my $url = $relay\->relay_url;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the relay\*(Aqs own WebSocket URL, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if not set.
Used for NIP\-42 relay tag validation.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    my $relay = Net::Nostr::Relay\->new(relay_url => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com/\*(Aq);
\&    $relay\->start(\*(Aq0.0.0.0\*(Aq, 8080);
.Ve
.SS relay_info
.IX Subsection "relay_info"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = $relay\->relay_info;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the Net::Nostr::RelayInfo object (NIP\-11), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if not set.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    my $relay = Net::Nostr::Relay\->new(
\&        relay_info => Net::Nostr::RelayInfo\->new(name => \*(AqMy Relay\*(Aq),
\&    );
\&    $relay\->start(\*(Aq0.0.0.0\*(Aq, 8080);
\&
\&    # Clients can now fetch: curl \-H \*(AqAccept: application/nostr+json\*(Aq http://localhost:8080/
.Ve
.SS max_subscriptions
.IX Subsection "max_subscriptions"
.Vb 1
\&    my $max = $relay\->max_subscriptions;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the per\-connection subscription limit, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if unlimited.
.SS max_filters
.IX Subsection "max_filters"
.Vb 1
\&    my $max = $relay\->max_filters;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the per\-REQ/COUNT filter count limit, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if unlimited.
.SS max_content_length
.IX Subsection "max_content_length"
.Vb 1
\&    my $max = $relay\->max_content_length;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the maximum event content length in bytes, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if unlimited.
.SS max_event_tags
.IX Subsection "max_event_tags"
.Vb 1
\&    my $max = $relay\->max_event_tags;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the maximum event tag count, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if unlimited.
.SS max_limit
.IX Subsection "max_limit"
.Vb 1
\&    my $max = $relay\->max_limit;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the server\-side cap on filter \f(CW\*(C`limit\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if no cap.
.SS default_limit
.IX Subsection "default_limit"
.Vb 1
\&    my $default = $relay\->default_limit;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the default limit applied to filters without one, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS created_at_lower_limit
.IX Subsection "created_at_lower_limit"
.Vb 1
\&    my $secs = $relay\->created_at_lower_limit;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the maximum event age in seconds, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if no bound.
.SS created_at_upper_limit
.IX Subsection "created_at_upper_limit"
.Vb 1
\&    my $secs = $relay\->created_at_upper_limit;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the maximum seconds\-into\-future for events, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if no bound.
.SS max_message_length
.IX Subsection "max_message_length"
.Vb 1
\&    my $max = $relay\->max_message_length;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the maximum incoming message size in bytes, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if unlimited.
.SS on_event
.IX Subsection "on_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $cb = $relay\->on_event;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the event policy callback, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if not set.
.SS idle_timeout
.IX Subsection "idle_timeout"
.Vb 1
\&    my $secs = $relay\->idle_timeout;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the idle timeout in seconds, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if not set.
.SS shutdown_timeout
.IX Subsection "shutdown_timeout"
.Vb 1
\&    my $secs = $relay\->shutdown_timeout;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the graceful shutdown drain period in seconds, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if not set.
.SS authenticated_pubkeys
.IX Subsection "authenticated_pubkeys"
.Vb 1
\&    my $auth = $relay\->authenticated_pubkeys;  # deep snapshot
.Ve
.PP
Returns a deep copy of authenticated pubkeys per connection (NIP\-42).
Mutating the returned hashref does not affect the relay\*(Aqs internal state.
Keys are connection IDs, values are hashrefs of pubkey hex strings.
.PP
.Vb 6
\&    my $auth = $relay\->authenticated_pubkeys;
\&    for my $conn_id (keys %$auth) {
\&        for my $pubkey (keys %{$auth\->{$conn_id}}) {
\&            say "Connection $conn_id authenticated as $pubkey";
\&        }
\&    }
.Ve
